{"id":44,"parent_id":34,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":44,"title":"Mark 10: True Greatness","subtitle":"","short_title":"Mark 10: True Greatness","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-10-true-greatness","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-10-true-greatness"},[".heading",{"id":"head11","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-10-true-greatness.head11"},["h1","Mark 10"],[".subtitle","True Greatness"],[".intro","Many Jews confused Old Testament prophecies about the first coming of the Messiah with prophecies about His Second Coming. They were looking for a Messiah to come with great power and glory as a conquering king to destroy their enemies. Christ did come to destroy their most important enemies—sin and death—but He would conquer those enemies by His own suffering and death was difficult for most to understand. This was foretold in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/53"},"Isaiah 53"],". Look for ways Jesus tried to teach these principles in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/10"},"Mark 10"],"."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Other Accounts of What You Read in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/10"},"Mark 10"]],["p.para",{"id":"p235","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-10-true-greatness.p235"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/10.1-31"},"Mark 10:1–31"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/19"},"Matthew 19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/18.15-30"},"Luke 18:15–30"]],["p.para",{"id":"p236","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-10-true-greatness.p236"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/10.32-52"},"Mark 10:32–52"],